main event: On May 1, 1952, AEC employees in Moses Lake, Washington, reported an observation of a single silver object flying in a straight line away from the observer for 1 1/2 minutes.
interesting points: The object did not have wings and made no sound.
It was visible for 1 1/2 minutes to a ground observer in the area.
The report mentions the presence of a patrol plane in the air at the same time as the sighting.
There were no radar contacts or photographs of the object.
The source of the report was deemed to be a civilian witness.
